This paper deals with interference coordination in cellular networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also uses tools from stochastic geometry (cs.SY) to analyze the performance of the network. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of cluster size and feedback allocation, which could fall under machine learning (cs.MM) and machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
